WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.473 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.473 --> 00:00:07.455 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:07.455 --> 00:00:17.808 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.808 --> 00:00:19.850 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:19.850 --> 00:00:23.305 align:middle line:10%
Courtney McInvale is with
us, a former FBI analyst

00:00:23.305 --> 00:00:24.680 align:middle line:10%
and she worked
for the Department

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:26.060 align:middle line:10%
of Homeland Security.

00:00:26.060 --> 00:00:30.200 align:middle line:84%
Most recently, she founded the
Seaside Shadows Haunted History

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:34.850 align:middle line:84%
Tours, and she's a licensed tour
guide, historian, and published

00:00:34.850 --> 00:00:36.410 align:middle line:90%
author on the paranormal.

00:00:36.410 --> 00:00:38.090 align:middle line:84%
Courtney, welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:38.090 --> 00:00:39.740 align:middle line:84%
>>COURTNEY MCINVALE: Thank
you so much for having me.

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:41.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How in
the world did you

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:44.060 align:middle line:84%
go from being an FBI
analyst to somebody

00:00:44.060 --> 00:00:46.040 align:middle line:90%
interested in haunted tours?

00:00:46.040 --> 00:00:48.680 align:middle line:10%
>>MCINVALE: I would say
that, actually, my interest

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:52.340 align:middle line:10%
in the paranormal and haunted
history came before my job

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:53.600 align:middle line:10%
with the government.

00:00:53.600 --> 00:00:57.290 align:middle line:10%
I grew up in a house that had
a lot of haunting activity,

00:00:57.290 --> 00:01:01.850 align:middle line:10%
and I was always sort of
searching for answers for what

00:01:01.850 --> 00:01:03.990 align:middle line:10%
had happened there and why.

00:01:03.990 --> 00:01:06.080 align:middle line:84%
And so working
for the government

00:01:06.080 --> 00:01:08.030 align:middle line:84%
and putting together
puzzle pieces,

00:01:08.030 --> 00:01:11.797 align:middle line:84%
coincided nicely with that sort
of research part of my brain.

00:01:11.797 --> 00:01:14.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You must have had a
passion for the paranormal.

00:01:14.130 --> 00:01:15.990 align:middle line:90%
What started this for you?

00:01:15.990 --> 00:01:18.540 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So when
I grew up, I grew up

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:20.610 align:middle line:84%
in a house in a small
town in Connecticut

00:01:20.610 --> 00:01:23.520 align:middle line:84%
that had a lot of activity
that was inexplicable.

00:01:23.520 --> 00:01:27.180 align:middle line:84%
And then as I got older, the
activity got kind of dark.

00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:30.120 align:middle line:84%
For a variety of reasons
there was a dark energy

00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:31.540 align:middle line:90%
that seemed to happen.

00:01:31.540 --> 00:01:33.870 align:middle line:84%
And it ended up when
I was a teenager,

00:01:33.870 --> 00:01:36.960 align:middle line:84%
that my mom called Ed and
Lorraine Warren to come

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:38.640 align:middle line:90%
to the house and check it out.

00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:40.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Giants in
the field, Giants.

00:01:40.380 --> 00:01:42.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Giants,
yes, yes, but we

00:01:42.360 --> 00:01:44.580 align:middle line:90%
didn't know that at the time.

00:01:44.580 --> 00:01:48.390 align:middle line:84%
We were kind of just
suffering this haunting,

00:01:48.390 --> 00:01:51.120 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, without
any knowledge of what

00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:52.320 align:middle line:90%
to do about it.

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:54.490 align:middle line:84%
And there was a lot
going on in our family.

00:01:54.490 --> 00:01:57.270 align:middle line:84%
And so when someone told
my mom that Ed and Lorraine

00:01:57.270 --> 00:02:00.910 align:middle line:84%
Warren lived in Connecticut,
and they were Catholic like us,

00:02:00.910 --> 00:02:04.453 align:middle line:84%
and they did ghost hunting,
she immediately called them.

00:02:04.453 --> 00:02:05.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Tell us more.

00:02:05.370 --> 00:02:06.360 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:08.639 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So it started
off, when I was growing up,

00:02:08.639 --> 00:02:10.590 align:middle line:84%
just like I call
an old New England

00:02:10.590 --> 00:02:14.280 align:middle line:84%
haunting with creaky
floorboards or doorknobs

00:02:14.280 --> 00:02:16.110 align:middle line:90%
jiggling or flickering lights.

00:02:16.110 --> 00:02:19.740 align:middle line:84%
And my mother would just say,
old houses do strange things.

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:24.210 align:middle line:84%
And it was never anything
too spooky or scary,

00:02:24.210 --> 00:02:28.200 align:middle line:84%
just evidence that perhaps
people had lived there before.

00:02:28.200 --> 00:02:29.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Not too
shocking, right?

00:02:29.730 --> 00:02:31.313 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: No, and
it wasn't anything

00:02:31.313 --> 00:02:34.150 align:middle line:84%
that made us lose sleep at
night or anything like that

00:02:34.150 --> 00:02:37.920 align:middle line:84%
and you know, so maybe just
the idea that an old house had

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.810 align:middle line:90%
little bits of the past left.

00:02:39.810 --> 00:02:41.370 align:middle line:84%
And then when I was
a teenager, there

00:02:41.370 --> 00:02:43.180 align:middle line:84%
was a lot going
on with my family.

00:02:43.180 --> 00:02:46.860 align:middle line:84%
My father was suffering from
different health conditions,

00:02:46.860 --> 00:02:50.520 align:middle line:84%
mental health, and him and
my mother were separating.

00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And he was working a job
called postmortem cleanup

00:02:53.610 --> 00:02:56.040 align:middle line:84%
where he was cleaning
up homicide and suicide.

00:02:56.040 --> 00:02:57.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Oh, what
a horrible job.

00:02:57.480 --> 00:02:59.710 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, he was
a police officer before.

00:02:59.710 --> 00:03:03.910 align:middle line:84%
So he felt like he could kind
of handle that sort of thing.

00:03:03.910 --> 00:03:05.655 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But he
couldn't, could he?

00:03:05.655 --> 00:03:11.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I think that a
darkness maybe found something

00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:13.170 align:middle line:90%
inside him during that time.

00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:14.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:03:14.370 --> 00:03:16.440 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And that's
when the activity really

00:03:16.440 --> 00:03:17.640 align:middle line:90%
escalated at the house.

00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:21.630 align:middle line:84%
So I always tell people it's
a perfect storm of events.

00:03:21.630 --> 00:03:24.990 align:middle line:84%
And I grew up very close
to both my parents.

00:03:24.990 --> 00:03:28.720 align:middle line:84%
And I definitely saw a change
in my dad at that time.

00:03:28.720 --> 00:03:31.050 align:middle line:84%
And we started to
have activity that

00:03:31.050 --> 00:03:35.610 align:middle line:84%
was more things like there
was weird sort of blood

00:03:35.610 --> 00:03:37.968 align:middle line:90%
on the wall, furniture moving.

00:03:37.968 --> 00:03:40.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Blood on the wall,
just appeared from nowhere?

00:03:40.260 --> 00:03:42.000 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Out of nowhere.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And other people
witnessed it, not just me.

00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:46.290 align:middle line:84%
My poor mother was
so worried about us,

00:03:46.290 --> 00:03:48.540 align:middle line:84%
she was bringing us for
mental health checks

00:03:48.540 --> 00:03:51.210 align:middle line:84%
when we first saw it to
psychiatrists to make sure

00:03:51.210 --> 00:03:55.260 align:middle line:84%
that we weren't all just in some
sort of weird delusional house.

00:03:55.260 --> 00:03:58.650 align:middle line:84%
And then my father,
of course, he

00:03:58.650 --> 00:04:00.330 align:middle line:84%
was getting help
for what he had.

00:04:00.330 --> 00:04:02.850 align:middle line:84%
But my parents ended
up getting divorced.

00:04:02.850 --> 00:04:05.910 align:middle line:84%
And then when this
all sort of happened,

00:04:05.910 --> 00:04:09.330 align:middle line:84%
the activity continued
with shadow figures,

00:04:09.330 --> 00:04:13.950 align:middle line:84%
and what appeared to just be
things that weren't, I guess,

00:04:13.950 --> 00:04:16.839 align:middle line:84%
maybe positive or
there to support us.

00:04:16.839 --> 00:04:18.690 align:middle line:84%
And so my mom, the
first thing she did

00:04:18.690 --> 00:04:20.550 align:middle line:90%
was call a local priest.

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:21.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Help, help.

00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:24.750 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yes, yes, she kind
of kept it low because she was

00:04:24.750 --> 00:04:27.210 align:middle line:84%
a school teacher, and my dad
had been a police officer,

00:04:27.210 --> 00:04:30.010 align:middle line:84%
so being public servants, They
didn't want to advertise a huge

00:04:30.010 --> 00:04:30.810 align:middle line:90%
haunting--

00:04:30.810 --> 00:04:31.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:04:31.470 --> 00:04:33.220 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: --and have
that reflect on us.

00:04:33.220 --> 00:04:34.380 align:middle line:90%
So she calls the priest.

00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:36.840 align:middle line:84%
The priest comes does
the blessing, But.

00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:38.230 align:middle line:90%
He witnessed some activity.

00:04:38.230 --> 00:04:42.520 align:middle line:84%
So he kindly told my mother that
this was beyond his abilities

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:43.320 align:middle line:90%
at that time.

00:04:43.320 --> 00:04:44.612 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He wasn't an exorcist.

00:04:44.612 --> 00:04:45.445 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Exactly.

00:04:45.445 --> 00:04:46.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He was just a priest.

00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:49.290 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Right, right,
he's the local parish priest.

00:04:49.290 --> 00:04:51.577 align:middle line:84%
So he's thinking, you
know, I've done my part.

00:04:51.577 --> 00:04:53.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He gives
communion, you know.

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:53.760 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: (LAUGHING) Yeah.

00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:54.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Confession.

00:04:54.610 --> 00:04:55.860 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: This is it, right?

00:04:55.860 --> 00:04:57.810 align:middle line:90%
I sprinkled some holy water.

00:04:57.810 --> 00:05:00.250 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to be on my way.

00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:03.270 align:middle line:84%
So she didn't know what to
do because that didn't really

00:05:03.270 --> 00:05:04.590 align:middle line:90%
change anything.

00:05:04.590 --> 00:05:07.060 align:middle line:84%
We were still having
activity off and on.

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:09.360 align:middle line:84%
And then she called
a pastor that was

00:05:09.360 --> 00:05:10.980 align:middle line:90%
recommended to her by friends.

00:05:10.980 --> 00:05:13.770 align:middle line:84%
And he did go into
the house, and he

00:05:13.770 --> 00:05:15.680 align:middle line:84%
went into what was
my childhood bedroom.

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:17.430 align:middle line:84%
And I guess he was
interested in this room

00:05:17.430 --> 00:05:20.070 align:middle line:84%
because my rosary beads
had broken in that room

00:05:20.070 --> 00:05:21.290 align:middle line:90%
and things of that nature.

00:05:21.290 --> 00:05:22.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:05:22.090 --> 00:05:24.480 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So he says
in there that he finds

00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:25.980 align:middle line:90%
the cause of the haunting.

00:05:25.980 --> 00:05:31.050 align:middle line:84%
But what he more or less comes
back and says is, to my mother,

00:05:31.050 --> 00:05:33.820 align:middle line:84%
your daughter has Grateful
Dead posters on her wall, so,

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:34.620 align:middle line:90%
they probably--

00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:35.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Blame the posters.

00:05:35.860 --> 00:05:37.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah the
Grateful Dead posters

00:05:37.610 --> 00:05:40.110 align:middle line:90%
brought in demons he tells her.

00:05:40.110 --> 00:05:43.950 align:middle line:84%
Needless to say, despite my mom
being better safe than sorry

00:05:43.950 --> 00:05:46.347 align:middle line:84%
and removing my
posters, this was not

00:05:46.347 --> 00:05:47.430 align:middle line:90%
the cause of our haunting.

00:05:47.430 --> 00:05:48.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's Jerry
Garcia's fault.

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:50.550 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: It was not.

00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:52.590 align:middle line:84%
When has a hippie
folk band ever haunted

00:05:52.590 --> 00:05:57.360 align:middle line:84%
somebody as house demonically,
right, so or whatever,

00:05:57.360 --> 00:05:58.240 align:middle line:90%
negatively.

00:05:58.240 --> 00:06:00.083 align:middle line:90%
So that didn't help.

00:06:00.083 --> 00:06:01.500 align:middle line:84%
And then that's
when she found out

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:02.910 align:middle line:90%
about Ed and Lorraine Warren.

00:06:02.910 --> 00:06:04.830 align:middle line:84%
The number was given
to her by someone,

00:06:04.830 --> 00:06:07.110 align:middle line:90%
and she gave them a call.

00:06:07.110 --> 00:06:09.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's how we
came to that point.

00:06:09.960 --> 00:06:11.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did they
come to the house?

00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:14.050 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, so Ed was
pretty sick at that time.

00:06:14.050 --> 00:06:17.430 align:middle line:84%
So Lorraine came as sort
of like the front person.

00:06:17.430 --> 00:06:19.710 align:middle line:84%
Funny enough,
before she came, she

00:06:19.710 --> 00:06:23.220 align:middle line:84%
told my mom to tell the
house that she was coming,

00:06:23.220 --> 00:06:25.440 align:middle line:84%
and the activity
got really quiet.

00:06:25.440 --> 00:06:28.200 align:middle line:84%
So my mom thought she had done
some miraculous prayer that

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:29.370 align:middle line:90%
had worked.

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:31.500 align:middle line:84%
But she said, no, if
it got quiet, honey,

00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:35.190 align:middle line:84%
that means that they
know I'm coming,

00:06:35.190 --> 00:06:36.750 align:middle line:90%
and they don't want me to.

00:06:36.750 --> 00:06:40.740 align:middle line:84%
And so she came with her team,
and she interviewed the family.

00:06:40.740 --> 00:06:44.040 align:middle line:90%
And she investigated the home.

00:06:44.040 --> 00:06:45.510 align:middle line:90%
She talked to me too.

00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:48.870 align:middle line:84%
She felt like I had some
anger at what was going on

00:06:48.870 --> 00:06:50.880 align:middle line:84%
in the house and with
my dad and talked

00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:53.430 align:middle line:84%
to me about the importance
of energy and emotions.

00:06:53.430 --> 00:06:56.190 align:middle line:84%
But she did think
our home had become

00:06:56.190 --> 00:06:58.170 align:middle line:90%
a train station for spirits.

00:06:58.170 --> 00:06:59.590 align:middle line:90%
And there were good ones.

00:06:59.590 --> 00:07:00.640 align:middle line:90%
There were bad ones.

00:07:00.640 --> 00:07:03.730 align:middle line:84%
There were bad ones that had
responded to a darkness that

00:07:03.730 --> 00:07:04.530 align:middle line:90%
had happened.

00:07:04.530 --> 00:07:05.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:07:05.330 --> 00:07:09.330 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And she was going
to get rid of that dark energy

00:07:09.330 --> 00:07:10.650 align:middle line:90%
with a cleansing of the home.

00:07:10.650 --> 00:07:12.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Courtney,
what do you think

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:14.940 align:middle line:84%
the impetus was for the
spirits to hit the home?

00:07:14.940 --> 00:07:16.315 align:middle line:84%
Not the Grateful
Dead, of course.

00:07:16.315 --> 00:07:17.732 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Not
the Grateful Dead.

00:07:17.732 --> 00:07:19.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But what did
you think was going on?

00:07:19.690 --> 00:07:21.150 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I think
that there was

00:07:21.150 --> 00:07:25.470 align:middle line:84%
a lot of emotion in my
family about worrying

00:07:25.470 --> 00:07:27.720 align:middle line:90%
about my dad's mental health.

00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:31.020 align:middle line:84%
I think his job at
that time, and things

00:07:31.020 --> 00:07:34.110 align:middle line:84%
he was taking from his
job, at that time, all sort

00:07:34.110 --> 00:07:37.050 align:middle line:84%
of collided into a place
that was already a little bit

00:07:37.050 --> 00:07:39.215 align:middle line:84%
energetically prepared
to be haunted.

00:07:39.215 --> 00:07:40.590 align:middle line:84%
Because we had
that minute stuff.

00:07:40.590 --> 00:07:42.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you think
they followed your father,

00:07:42.590 --> 00:07:43.860 align:middle line:90%
basically, to the house.

00:07:43.860 --> 00:07:46.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I think so, and
I think, my poor father,

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:48.070 align:middle line:90%
he also suffered addiction.

00:07:48.070 --> 00:07:50.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think they
saw this darkness,

00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:54.837 align:middle line:84%
and it almost
perpetuated that darkness

00:07:54.837 --> 00:07:55.920 align:middle line:90%
and made it worse for him.

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:58.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What
addiction did he have?

00:07:58.050 --> 00:08:01.510 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: To medications that
he was given for mental health.

00:08:01.510 --> 00:08:02.310 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:08:02.310 --> 00:08:04.410 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah,
yeah, and I think

00:08:04.410 --> 00:08:11.040 align:middle line:84%
that an energy sort of saw an
opportunity there to come in.

00:08:11.040 --> 00:08:12.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does the family
still own the house?

00:08:12.960 --> 00:08:16.050 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: No, my
mother did sell it.

00:08:16.050 --> 00:08:20.170 align:middle line:84%
When I went to college,
and I was studying abroad,

00:08:20.170 --> 00:08:21.300 align:middle line:90%
she sold the house.

00:08:21.300 --> 00:08:23.700 align:middle line:84%
The activity had
started to resume.

00:08:23.700 --> 00:08:26.190 align:middle line:84%
My father passed
away shortly after.

00:08:26.190 --> 00:08:28.650 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't living in the
house when it got really bad.

00:08:28.650 --> 00:08:29.130 align:middle line:90%
OK,

00:08:29.130 --> 00:08:30.297 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sorry to hear that.

00:08:30.297 --> 00:08:31.410 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Thank you.

00:08:31.410 --> 00:08:34.350 align:middle line:84%
But Lorraine did
tell my mom that when

00:08:34.350 --> 00:08:38.190 align:middle line:84%
the house was sold, that
it could reopen things

00:08:38.190 --> 00:08:40.679 align:middle line:84%
because she had more
or less sort of created

00:08:40.679 --> 00:08:44.110 align:middle line:84%
a bubble around our
family and our life there.

00:08:44.110 --> 00:08:46.290 align:middle line:84%
But the house could
have retained energy.

00:08:46.290 --> 00:08:49.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Right, did you have
to disclose to the new buyers--

00:08:49.300 --> 00:08:50.100 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: No.

00:08:50.100 --> 00:08:53.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --that this was a--
in some states, you have to.

