00:15:15.600 --> 00:15:16.680 align:middle line:90%
Now, where were you?

00:15:16.680 --> 00:15:19.380 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: This was an
area known as Dudleytown

00:15:19.380 --> 00:15:24.270 align:middle line:84%
in Northwest Connecticut, which
is a ghost town, they call it.

00:15:24.270 --> 00:15:26.850 align:middle line:90%
It's an old abandoned town.

00:15:26.850 --> 00:15:28.350 align:middle line:90%
The ground wasn't fertile.

00:15:28.350 --> 00:15:30.750 align:middle line:84%
People didn't really
have a great opportunity

00:15:30.750 --> 00:15:33.580 align:middle line:84%
there after the Revolutionary
War when they were building.

00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:35.400 align:middle line:84%
However, a lot of
the people that did

00:15:35.400 --> 00:15:37.950 align:middle line:84%
live there reported that
that was not really why

00:15:37.950 --> 00:15:39.510 align:middle line:90%
the town became a ghost town.

00:15:39.510 --> 00:15:41.400 align:middle line:90%
People were going mad up there.

00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:42.760 align:middle line:90%
They were murdering each other.

00:15:42.760 --> 00:15:43.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:15:43.560 --> 00:15:45.960 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: They would come
home and find each other

00:15:45.960 --> 00:15:49.770 align:middle line:84%
in maniacal laughter, so
no one lives in that area.

00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:55.320 align:middle line:84%
There's some homes, and they
call themselves the Dark Forest

00:15:55.320 --> 00:15:58.560 align:middle line:84%
Association, and they employ
police to keep people out

00:15:58.560 --> 00:16:00.820 align:middle line:84%
of the forest when they're
not supposed to be.

00:16:00.820 --> 00:16:03.390 align:middle line:84%
But there is a nature trail
now that goes through it,

00:16:03.390 --> 00:16:07.000 align:middle line:84%
and you can go see the old
foundations of Dudleytown.

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:08.822 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who would want to?

00:16:08.822 --> 00:16:13.030 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Me, [LAUGHS]
I just want to know why

00:16:13.030 --> 00:16:15.250 align:middle line:84%
and what happened
and if it's true.

00:16:15.250 --> 00:16:18.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, this app that
you had, how was it developed?

00:16:18.610 --> 00:16:23.570 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So it's developed in
the same thing as a spirit box

00:16:23.570 --> 00:16:24.370 align:middle line:90%
sort of.

00:16:24.370 --> 00:16:27.040 align:middle line:84%
Like I was saying, a spirit box
sweeps through radio stations

00:16:27.040 --> 00:16:29.830 align:middle line:84%
rapidly to generate
white noise to allow

00:16:29.830 --> 00:16:31.330 align:middle line:90%
spirits to communicate.

00:16:31.330 --> 00:16:35.290 align:middle line:84%
This sweeps through frequencies
to generate something

00:16:35.290 --> 00:16:38.230 align:middle line:84%
that spirits can manipulate so
that their voices reverberate

00:16:38.230 --> 00:16:39.610 align:middle line:90%
back in an echo.

00:16:39.610 --> 00:16:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Clearly there
was some kind of voice

00:16:41.770 --> 00:16:43.750 align:middle line:90%
trying to communicate with you.

00:16:43.750 --> 00:16:44.905 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, yeah.

00:16:44.905 --> 00:16:46.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You could hear it.

00:16:46.030 --> 00:16:49.220 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, and I love
when they communicate with me.

00:16:49.220 --> 00:16:51.010 align:middle line:84%
I call that sort of
an active haunting,

00:16:51.010 --> 00:16:55.270 align:middle line:84%
meaning that they
see me, and they

00:16:55.270 --> 00:16:57.670 align:middle line:84%
know that I'm talking to
them, and they hear me.

00:16:57.670 --> 00:16:59.710 align:middle line:84%
And they're answering
me intelligently,

00:16:59.710 --> 00:17:02.050 align:middle line:84%
and that means that they
probably know they're dead,

00:17:02.050 --> 00:17:04.172 align:middle line:84%
or they're trying to convey
some sort of message.

00:17:04.172 --> 00:17:06.339 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Courtney, what
allowed you to start flowing

00:17:06.339 --> 00:17:08.520 align:middle line:90%
into investigate battlefields?

00:17:08.520 --> 00:17:11.760 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: That had a
lot to do with my work

00:17:11.760 --> 00:17:13.829 align:middle line:84%
at Seaside Shadows,
but I also have

00:17:13.829 --> 00:17:15.240 align:middle line:90%
to credit my father with that.

00:17:15.240 --> 00:17:18.089 align:middle line:90%
He raised me on Civil War books.

00:17:18.089 --> 00:17:22.050 align:middle line:84%
And after I had written about
Connecticut and the places I

00:17:22.050 --> 00:17:24.270 align:middle line:84%
was investigating
there, I thought

00:17:24.270 --> 00:17:26.910 align:middle line:84%
I would love to
investigate the Civil War.

00:17:26.910 --> 00:17:30.960 align:middle line:84%
But in addition to that,
it was during COVID

00:17:30.960 --> 00:17:34.140 align:middle line:84%
that I had this
really strange dream.

00:17:34.140 --> 00:17:36.060 align:middle line:84%
The Civil War wasn't
sort of on my brain.

00:17:36.060 --> 00:17:37.102 align:middle line:90%
That's in the background.

00:17:37.102 --> 00:17:37.902 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All right.

00:17:37.902 --> 00:17:40.350 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And during COVID,
I was making video segments

00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:43.770 align:middle line:84%
like this where I was
investigating haunted places

00:17:43.770 --> 00:17:46.390 align:middle line:84%
or going to cemeteries
and sharing stories.

00:17:46.390 --> 00:17:48.420 align:middle line:84%
And I was scheduled
with my husband who

00:17:48.420 --> 00:17:50.670 align:middle line:84%
