appeared to me in this dream
in Union Civil War uniform.

00:18:02.400 --> 00:18:04.800 align:middle line:90%
And they were young.

00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:10.250 align:middle line:84%
And in the dream, they conveyed
to me that they lived nearby.

00:18:10.250 --> 00:18:12.370 align:middle line:90%
And that I had to find them.

00:18:12.370 --> 00:18:14.410 align:middle line:90%
That their stone was nearby.

00:18:14.410 --> 00:18:17.530 align:middle line:84%
And I could tell that
they were Civil War,

00:18:17.530 --> 00:18:19.000 align:middle line:84%
and they said they
were brothers.

00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:21.220 align:middle line:84%
So I woke up not
remembering much else

00:18:21.220 --> 00:18:23.540 align:middle line:84%
from the dream other than
that, and told my husband

00:18:23.540 --> 00:18:26.290 align:middle line:84%
we have to find these two
brothers that lived near here

00:18:26.290 --> 00:18:27.940 align:middle line:90%
who died during the Civil War.

00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:30.670 align:middle line:84%
And he said, no, you're
filming Abigail today.

00:18:30.670 --> 00:18:31.720 align:middle line:90%
We're not doing that.

00:18:31.720 --> 00:18:32.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:18:32.110 --> 00:18:33.693 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: But I
went and found them.

00:18:33.693 --> 00:18:36.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why do you
think they contacted you?

00:18:36.330 --> 00:18:38.330 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I think
that they were

00:18:38.330 --> 00:18:40.340 align:middle line:84%
ready for their
story to be shared

00:18:40.340 --> 00:18:42.020 align:middle line:90%
and for them to be remembered.

00:18:42.020 --> 00:18:45.170 align:middle line:84%
And I think they were
leading me into sharing

00:18:45.170 --> 00:18:47.510 align:middle line:84%
the stories of so many like
them whose stories have

00:18:47.510 --> 00:18:48.590 align:middle line:90%
been forgotten.

00:18:48.590 --> 00:18:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And I was able to
find their monuments,

00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:54.650 align:middle line:84%
find out what happened to them,
find their graves from where

00:18:54.650 --> 00:18:57.530 align:middle line:84%
they were imprisoned
and where they died

00:18:57.530 --> 00:18:59.570 align:middle line:90%
and share their story.

00:18:59.570 --> 00:19:02.450 align:middle line:84%
And that led me to find the
stories of so many others.

00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:03.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Remarkable.

00:19:03.380 --> 00:19:04.180 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:19:04.180 --> 00:19:05.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Spirit boxes.

00:19:05.370 --> 00:19:06.170 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:19:06.170 --> 00:19:07.253 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You've used them.

00:19:07.253 --> 00:19:08.053 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:19:08.053 --> 00:19:09.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You like them?

00:19:09.050 --> 00:19:09.920 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I do.

00:19:09.920 --> 00:19:10.720 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:19:10.720 --> 00:19:12.920 align:middle line:84%
I think you have to be
cautious in that you're not

00:19:12.920 --> 00:19:17.030 align:middle line:84%
hearing the radio and
mistaking that for a spirit.

00:19:17.030 --> 00:19:20.255 align:middle line:84%
I think you have to make
sure you get really responses

00:19:20.255 --> 00:19:21.380 align:middle line:90%
that are responding to you.

00:19:21.380 --> 00:19:24.110 align:middle line:84%
But I do think it's a
great opportunity for us,

00:19:24.110 --> 00:19:26.660 align:middle line:84%
in real time, to hear
a voice from the past.

00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:30.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because if it's not a
voice from a past, what is it,

00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:31.670 align:middle line:90%
interference?

00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:33.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: It could
be interference.

00:19:33.500 --> 00:19:34.940 align:middle line:90%
It could be a radio wave.

00:19:34.940 --> 00:19:37.560 align:middle line:84%
That's why I tell people,
listen for multiple sweeps

00:19:37.560 --> 00:19:39.630 align:middle line:84%
because it's sweeping
through the radio.

00:19:39.630 --> 00:19:42.120 align:middle line:84%
So you want to hear a voice
over multiple syllables,

00:19:42.120 --> 00:19:45.750 align:middle line:84%
so you don't mistake it with a
song or a radio thing that's--

00:19:45.750 --> 00:19:46.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or my show.

00:19:46.680 --> 00:19:48.210 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Right, that
could come through.

00:19:48.210 --> 00:19:48.930 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:19:48.930 --> 00:19:51.090 align:middle line:84%
If I heard your voice, I don't
want to call you a ghost,

00:19:51.090 --> 00:19:51.480 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:19:51.480 --> 00:19:54.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, we have a clip
of you Courtney actually hearing

00:19:54.120 --> 00:19:54.930 align:middle line:90%
a ghost--

00:19:54.930 --> 00:19:55.380 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:19:55.380 --> 00:19:56.310 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --on a battlefield.

00:19:56.310 --> 00:19:57.110 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:19:57.110 --> 00:19:58.230 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:19:58.230 --> 00:20:01.380 align:middle line:10%
- Were you taken by surprise
attack from the Confederates?

00:20:01.380 --> 00:20:08.749 align:middle line:10%
[NOISE] From where
did they come?

00:20:08.749 --> 00:20:18.780 align:middle line:10%
[NOISE] Where were
you attacked from?

00:20:18.780 --> 00:20:29.500 align:middle line:10%
[NOISE] On your left.

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:30.880 align:middle line:90%
On our left.

00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:31.690 align:middle line:90%
[PLAYBACK ENDS]

00:20:31.690 --> 00:20:35.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What did we
just see and hear?

00:20:35.110 --> 00:20:38.110 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So that is at
the Antietam Battlefield,

00:20:38.110 --> 00:20:40.600 align:middle line:84%
and that was considered
the bloodiest day

00:20:40.600 --> 00:20:43.840 align:middle line:90%
in America, September 17, 1862.

00:20:43.840 --> 00:20:46.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tragic, lost
thousands, didn't we?

00:20:46.420 --> 00:20:47.950 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: 20,000 casualties.

00:20:47.950 --> 00:20:49.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:52.210 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: It was terrible,
and that was General Mansfield.

00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:54.757 align:middle line:84%
Now, General Mansfield,
he was from Connecticut.

00:20:54.757 --> 00:20:57.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You think that was the
General coming through to you?

00:20:57.340 --> 00:21:00.010 align:middle line:10%
>>MCINVALE: I do because I was
standing where he was mortally

00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:02.990 align:middle line:10%
wounded, at that exact spot.

00:21:02.990 --> 00:21:06.910 align:middle line:10%
And I was asking him, as I
was standing at that spot

00:21:06.910 --> 00:21:10.000 align:middle line:10%
where he was shot from,
and he answered that.

00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:12.280 align:middle line:84%
And I was already
intuitively looking

00:21:12.280 --> 00:21:13.720 align:middle line:84%
in that direction
thinking, yeah,

00:21:13.720 --> 00:21:15.280 align:middle line:84%
that's where they
might have hidden,

00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:17.080 align:middle line:90%
and no one would have noticed.

00:21:17.080 --> 00:21:19.480 align:middle line:84%
But what made me know
that it was really

00:21:19.480 --> 00:21:22.310 align:middle line:84%
him wouldn't come
until weeks later.

00:21:22.310 --> 00:21:26.590 align:middle line:84%
I was researching his story
at the Historical Society

00:21:26.590 --> 00:21:28.960 align:middle line:84%
that actually sits in
his home in Connecticut.

00:21:28.960 --> 00:21:31.870 align:middle line:84%
And they had the letters that
were sent home to his wife.

00:21:31.870 --> 00:21:35.050 align:middle line:84%
And all of the soldiers
that remarked to his wife,

00:21:35.050 --> 00:21:37.780 align:middle line:84%
as was tradition at the time,
to say what happened to him,

00:21:37.780 --> 00:21:41.470 align:middle line:84%
said that he was
yelling when he was shot

00:21:41.470 --> 00:21:43.853 align:middle line:90%
that he was shot from his left.

00:21:43.853 --> 00:21:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And then it was
published in the papers.

00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:46.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that's
what he was saying.

00:21:46.330 --> 00:21:48.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: His last words
were, "from your left."

00:21:48.650 --> 00:21:50.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
think he wanted with you?

00:21:50.720 --> 00:21:54.130 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I think he
was just answering me

00:21:54.130 --> 00:21:56.650 align:middle line:84%
about his story to make sure
I understood what happened.

00:21:56.650 --> 00:21:59.770 align:middle line:84%
I found out that, for him,
on that day at the battle,

00:21:59.770 --> 00:22:01.840 align:middle line:84%
other generals weren't
listening to him.

00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.910 align:middle line:84%
He had an instinct
and intuition,

00:22:03.910 --> 00:22:06.040 align:middle line:84%
and he was trying
to protect everyone.

00:22:06.040 --> 00:22:09.760 align:middle line:84%
And it was disregarded because
it was early in the war.

00:22:09.760 --> 00:22:12.550 align:middle line:84%
And I think he's trying to
say, I knew they were there,

00:22:12.550 --> 00:22:14.170 align:middle line:90%
and I'm still here too.

00:22:14.170 --> 00:22:16.562 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ulysses S Grant--

00:22:16.562 --> 00:22:17.520 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I love him.

00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:19.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --had an
interesting wife.

00:22:19.250 --> 00:22:20.650 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: He did, Julia.

00:22:20.650 --> 00:22:23.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And she had a lot of
premonitions about his death,

00:22:23.530 --> 00:22:24.610 align:middle line:90%
did she not?

00:22:24.610 --> 00:22:26.740 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: She had a
premonition about him

00:22:26.740 --> 00:22:28.600 align:middle line:90%
and Lincoln, to be honest.

00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:31.540 align:middle line:84%
This was one of my favorite
stories that I ever heard.

00:22:31.540 --> 00:22:33.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And Lincoln had a
dream about his own death.

00:22:33.770 --> 00:22:34.650 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: He sure did.

00:22:34.650 --> 00:22:35.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We'll get into that.

00:22:35.460 --> 00:22:36.460 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: He sure did.

00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:41.330 align:middle line:84%
So Julia didn't get along
with Mary Todd Lincoln.

00:22:41.330 --> 00:22:43.100 align:middle line:90%
They weren't best friends.

00:22:43.100 --> 00:22:48.362 align:middle line:84%
But Grant, who was, of course,
the Union General and Commander

00:22:48.362 --> 00:22:49.820 align:middle line:84%
for the Union during
the Civil War,

00:22:49.820 --> 00:22:51.740 align:middle line:84%
was good friends
with Lincoln, right?

00:22:51.740 --> 00:22:54.020 align:middle line:84%
So Grant and Lincoln
would have some events

00:22:54.020 --> 00:22:56.990 align:middle line:84%
together after the end of the
war, like, public appearances.

00:22:56.990 --> 00:22:59.450 align:middle line:84%
They were due to
go to the theater

00:22:59.450 --> 00:23:01.470 align:middle line:84%
together on the night
Lincoln was shot.

00:23:01.470 --> 00:23:02.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:23:02.270 --> 00:23:05.030 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: However,
prior to that,

00:23:05.030 --> 00:23:09.620 align:middle line:84%
Julia had a dream that Lincoln
and her husband Ulysses

00:23:09.620 --> 00:23:10.790 align:middle line:90%
would be shot.

00:23:10.790 --> 00:23:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And she said to him, you're
not going to the theater.

00:23:14.750 --> 00:23:17.750 align:middle line:84%
To which he said, I
know, basically, you're

00:23:17.750 --> 00:23:19.848 align:middle line:84%
trying to avoid hanging
out with Mary Todd.

00:23:19.848 --> 00:23:21.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do you tell
the president no, right?

00:23:21.890 --> 00:23:23.730 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Right, like
we have to do this.

00:23:23.730 --> 00:23:26.105 align:middle line:84%
And she said tell him we have
to go home to our children.

00:23:26.105 --> 00:23:27.230 align:middle line:90%
We have to be safe.

00:23:27.230 --> 00:23:29.990 align:middle line:84%
And then a messenger came
to deliver the invitation

00:23:29.990 --> 00:23:32.630 align:middle line:84%
to the theater to their place
where they were staying.

00:23:32.630 --> 00:23:35.150 align:middle line:84%
And she said that messenger
is one of the party that's

00:23:35.150 --> 00:23:36.110 align:middle line:90%
going to kill Lincoln.

00:23:36.110 --> 00:23:37.310 align:middle line:90%
She knew it.

00:23:37.310 --> 00:23:39.770 align:middle line:84%
And sure enough,
Ulysses believes her.

00:23:39.770 --> 00:23:41.600 align:middle line:90%
He loves his wife very much.

00:23:41.600 --> 00:23:45.140 align:middle line:84%
And they left and told
Lincoln that they wouldn't

00:23:45.140 --> 00:23:46.430 align:middle line:90%
be able to go to the theater.

00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:48.620 align:middle line:84%
And Lincoln was shot
and killed that night.

00:23:48.620 --> 00:23:51.313 align:middle line:84%
And it was turned out
that Ulysses was supposed

00:23:51.313 --> 00:23:52.480 align:middle line:90%
to be killed that night too.

00:23:52.480 --> 00:23:55.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, both of them,
yeah, a double assassination.

00:23:55.190 --> 00:23:55.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:23:55.990 --> 00:23:59.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And Lincoln's dream was
he walked into the State Room

00:23:59.420 --> 00:24:00.270 align:middle line:90%
at the White House.

00:24:00.270 --> 00:24:01.070 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:24:01.070 --> 00:24:03.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And there was a
person in a casket surrounded

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:04.820 align:middle line:90%
by soldiers.

00:24:04.820 --> 00:24:06.410 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And he asked
who died, and they said,

00:24:06.410 --> 00:24:07.220 align:middle line:90%
the president.

00:24:07.220 --> 00:24:08.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And he looked
in, and it was him.

00:24:08.970 --> 00:24:09.980 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes, yeah.

00:24:09.980 --> 00:24:11.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's got
to be kind of jarring.

00:24:11.730 --> 00:24:13.880 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, and it
happened a week before,

00:24:13.880 --> 00:24:15.560 align:middle line:90%
and it happened more than once.

00:24:15.560 --> 00:24:18.290 align:middle line:84%
And Lincoln believed
in spiritualism too.

00:24:18.290 --> 00:24:21.080 align:middle line:84%
Him and Mary Todd had
seances in the White House

00:24:21.080 --> 00:24:22.620 align:middle line:90%
to communicate with their son.

00:24:22.620 --> 00:24:25.890 align:middle line:84%
They very much were a believer
in omens from the spirit world.

00:24:25.890 --> 00:24:27.062 align:middle line:90%
So he was unnerved.

00:24:27.062 --> 00:24:28.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell me
about the drumming

00:24:28.520 --> 00:24:30.500 align:middle line:90%
you heard at Gettysburg.

00:24:30.500 --> 00:24:35.470 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So Gettysburg is
this remarkable residual haunt.

00:24:35.470 --> 00:24:39.610 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like we step back
in time, or perhaps we do.

00:24:39.610 --> 00:24:40.610 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps we do.

00:24:40.610 --> 00:24:42.970 align:middle line:84%
And we can hear
what's happening there

00:24:42.970 --> 00:24:45.100 align:middle line:90%
as if we're at the battle.

00:24:45.100 --> 00:24:48.350 align:middle line:84%
And when I was at
Gettysburg, not long ago,

00:24:48.350 --> 00:24:50.170 align:middle line:84%
I walked onto the
wheat field, which

00:24:50.170 --> 00:24:52.460 align:middle line:84%
was a clash between
Georgia and Connecticut,

00:24:52.460 --> 00:24:54.610 align:middle line:84%
which is honestly the
people I'm writing about,

00:24:54.610 --> 00:24:56.080 align:middle line:90%
and I heard drumming.

00:24:56.080 --> 00:24:59.770 align:middle line:84%
It was so real, I thought that
it was re-enactors at first,

00:24:59.770 --> 00:25:01.960 align:middle line:84%
until I walked out
there and saw no one.

00:25:01.960 --> 00:25:04.390 align:middle line:84%
My husband drove
around to see if there

00:25:04.390 --> 00:25:06.310 align:middle line:84%
were any re-enactors
whose drums could

00:25:06.310 --> 00:25:07.480 align:middle line:90%
have been echoing through.

00:25:07.480 --> 00:25:09.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Like drumming of
a garrison or something

00:25:09.140 --> 00:25:09.400 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:25:09.400 --> 00:25:11.470 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Drumming
like marching into battle

00:25:11.470 --> 00:25:12.730 align:middle line:90%
or even a death march

00:25:12.730 --> 00:25:14.313 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Boom baba
boom ba ba bom bom.

00:25:14.313 --> 00:25:17.140 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And we heard a
couple different cadences.

00:25:17.140 --> 00:25:20.230 align:middle line:84%
And then it stopped, and
then it came back again.

00:25:20.230 --> 00:25:23.650 align:middle line:84%
And it was in a thunderstorm,
like, this electric energy,

00:25:23.650 --> 00:25:25.210 align:middle line:84%
and then you could
hear the drumming.

00:25:25.210 --> 00:25:26.585 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well,
they say a picture

00:25:26.585 --> 00:25:27.970 align:middle line:90%
is worth a thousand words.

00:25:27.970 --> 00:25:28.240 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:25:28.240 --> 00:25:30.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's look at
this experience you have.

00:25:30.220 --> 00:25:31.020 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:25:31.020 --> 00:25:43.155 align:middle line:90%


00:25:43.155 --> 00:25:45.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You could hear
drumming in the background.

00:25:45.280 --> 00:25:46.080 align:middle line:10%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:25:46.080 --> 00:25:49.970 align:middle line:90%


00:25:49.970 --> 00:25:51.590 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it's pretty incredible.

00:25:51.590 --> 00:25:52.490 align:middle line:90%
I get chills still.

00:25:52.490 --> 00:25:54.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do you
pick this up on video?

00:25:54.260 --> 00:25:56.630 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: [LAUGHS] I--

00:25:56.630 --> 00:25:57.798 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Are you a magnet?

00:25:57.798 --> 00:25:59.340 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I would
like to think so.

00:25:59.340 --> 00:26:01.100 align:middle line:84%
I spend a lot of
time on battlefields

00:26:01.100 --> 00:26:03.470 align:middle line:84%
trying to talk to spirits
and connect with them

00:26:03.470 --> 00:26:07.910 align:middle line:84%
and be open to them and hope
that they're receptive to me.

00:26:07.910 --> 00:26:11.870 align:middle line:84%
But I also just think that
there's some places where

00:26:11.870 --> 00:26:13.010 align:middle line:90%
we have this luck.

00:26:13.010 --> 00:26:15.560 align:middle line:84%
But I will tell you, my husband
and a friend were with me,

00:26:15.560 --> 00:26:18.160 align:middle line:84%
and their phones didn't
record the sound.

00:26:18.160 --> 00:26:19.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But you got it.

00:26:19.160 --> 00:26:20.480 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: But it came on mine.

00:26:20.480 --> 00:26:21.830 align:middle line:84%
And I was further
away from the sound.

00:26:21.830 --> 00:26:23.872 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you think all
battlefields, Courtney,

00:26:23.872 --> 00:26:25.770 align:middle line:90%
have ghosts?

00:26:25.770 --> 00:26:27.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I think
all battlefields

00:26:27.620 --> 00:26:30.890 align:middle line:84%
have energetic
heartbeats of history.

00:26:30.890 --> 00:26:33.940 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it's a
ghost who very much maybe

00:26:33.940 --> 00:26:34.940 align:middle line:90%
didn't know they passed.

00:26:34.940 --> 00:26:39.680 align:middle line:84%
But oftentimes, it's the
impact of all of these people

00:26:39.680 --> 00:26:42.320 align:middle line:84%
who clashed with each
other in utter violence

00:26:42.320 --> 00:26:43.760 align:middle line:90%
and hand-to-hand combat.

00:26:43.760 --> 00:26:46.307 align:middle line:84%
These young people who didn't
know they were going to die.

00:26:46.307 --> 00:26:47.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So much distress.

00:26:47.390 --> 00:26:48.980 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And that
energy, just sits there.

00:26:48.980 --> 00:26:50.162 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Negative, negative.

00:26:50.162 --> 00:26:51.870 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And it
can never go anywhere.

00:26:51.870 --> 00:26:52.910 align:middle line:90%
It will always be there.

00:26:52.910 --> 00:26:56.000 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what's
there and a reminder.

00:26:56.000 --> 00:26:58.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there a
certain time to see ghosts?

00:26:58.520 --> 00:27:01.770 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: You know, I have
luck at all different times.

00:27:01.770 --> 00:27:03.770 align:middle line:84%
With the drumming, I found
out that was actually

00:27:03.770 --> 00:27:05.870 align:middle line:84%
during the hours that the
clash in the wheat field

00:27:05.870 --> 00:27:07.170 align:middle line:90%
was occurring.

00:27:07.170 --> 00:27:10.190 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes maybe you
can have more occurrences

00:27:10.190 --> 00:27:11.540 align:middle line:90%
on an anniversary.

00:27:11.540 --> 00:27:16.470 align:middle line:84%
But really, if you're receptive,
I think it can be any time.

00:27:16.470 --> 00:27:19.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Antietam, of
course, had a battlefield

00:27:19.060 --> 00:27:21.060 align:middle line:90%
which was called Bloody Lane.

00:27:21.060 --> 00:27:22.240 align:middle line:90%
Tell me about that.

00:27:22.240 --> 00:27:24.390 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So Antietam
was a single-day battle,

00:27:24.390 --> 00:27:26.460 align:middle line:84%
unlike Gettysburg
which was three days.

00:27:26.460 --> 00:27:28.980 align:middle line:84%
But we kind of separate
when we look at battlefields

00:27:28.980 --> 00:27:31.710 align:middle line:84%
by areas where different
engagements happen

00:27:31.710 --> 00:27:32.880 align:middle line:90%
during a battle.

00:27:32.880 --> 00:27:36.630 align:middle line:84%
The Bloody Lane was just
known as the Sunken Road.

00:27:36.630 --> 00:27:39.930 align:middle line:84%
It was an old farm
road in rural Maryland.

00:27:39.930 --> 00:27:43.050 align:middle line:84%
And in the Bloody Lane
or the Sunken Road,

00:27:43.050 --> 00:27:45.573 align:middle line:84%
there were Confederates that
were sort of staged, you know,

00:27:45.573 --> 00:27:47.490 align:middle line:84%
like it was their trenches
with their weapons.

00:27:47.490 --> 00:27:50.220 align:middle line:84%
And the Union was going
to infiltrate into there,

00:27:50.220 --> 00:27:52.740 align:middle line:84%
and try to shoot those
Confederates, which they do.

00:27:52.740 --> 00:27:54.240 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Boy, you
know your history.

00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:57.060 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, and
the Union shoots them,

00:27:57.060 --> 00:27:58.030 align:middle line:90%
and they die in there.

00:27:58.030 --> 00:28:00.370 align:middle line:84%
But they shoot the Union,
and the Union falls in there.

00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:03.600 align:middle line:84%
So all their bodies
just get lined up here

00:28:03.600 --> 00:28:05.520 align:middle line:90%
piled on top of each other.

00:28:05.520 --> 00:28:07.980 align:middle line:84%
And the blood runs
through it, and this place

00:28:07.980 --> 00:28:10.770 align:middle line:84%
was never the same and always
sort of remained haunted.

00:28:10.770 --> 00:28:13.020 align:middle line:84%
And it became known
as the Bloody Lane.

00:28:13.020 --> 00:28:15.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And we have a
clip of you at Bloody Lane.

00:28:15.660 --> 00:28:16.655 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:28:16.655 --> 00:28:16.930 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:28:16.930 --> 00:28:18.370 align:middle line:10%
- Now, as for
paranormal activity,

00:28:18.370 --> 00:28:20.200 align:middle line:10%
there's quite a bit
of it reported here.

00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:22.780 align:middle line:10%
People report seeing
figures walking the lane,

00:28:22.780 --> 00:28:26.380 align:middle line:10%
seeing them laying down,
hearing crying, hearing moaning,

00:28:26.380 --> 00:28:28.480 align:middle line:10%
hearing attacks come
from the battlefield.

00:28:28.480 --> 00:28:31.360 align:middle line:84%
We just heard a park ranger talk
about a figure in white that

00:28:31.360 --> 00:28:33.130 align:middle line:84%
appeared that he
thought might have been

00:28:33.130 --> 00:28:34.720 align:middle line:90%
a Medal of Honor recipient.

00:28:34.720 --> 00:28:36.940 align:middle line:84%
But more commonly than
not, school field trips

00:28:36.940 --> 00:28:38.620 align:middle line:90%
report a lot of activity here.

00:28:38.620 --> 00:28:41.860 align:middle line:10%
And there was an Irish Brigade
led by a man from Ireland

00:28:41.860 --> 00:28:43.060 align:middle line:10%
on the Union side.

00:28:43.060 --> 00:28:46.600 align:middle line:10%
And he had a battle cry that
was [NON-ENGLISH] which sounds

00:28:46.600 --> 00:28:49.540 align:middle line:10%
a lot like, fa, la, la, la,
la or something like that from

00:28:49.540 --> 00:28:50.740 align:middle line:10%
a Christmas time.

00:28:50.740 --> 00:28:52.600 align:middle line:84%
So they ran up to their
teacher telling them

00:28:52.600 --> 00:28:56.110 align:middle line:84%
that they heard someone singing
Christmas carols in the field.

00:28:56.110 --> 00:28:58.330 align:middle line:10%
The teacher looked around
and of course, saw no one,

00:28:58.330 --> 00:29:00.950 align:middle line:10%
but then saw that
Irish battle cry.

00:29:00.950 --> 00:29:03.540 align:middle line:10%
This is the Bloody Lane.

00:29:03.540 --> 00:29:04.340 align:middle line:90%
[PLAYBACK ENDS]

00:29:04.340 --> 00:29:06.417 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You heard that
cry in the background,

00:29:06.417 --> 00:29:08.750 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, and I didn't
hear it when I was there.

00:29:08.750 --> 00:29:10.708 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, you sure
it's not some guy hiding

00:29:10.708 --> 00:29:12.558 align:middle line:90%
behind a tree going, wah.

00:29:12.558 --> 00:29:13.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Oh, yeah, I'm sure.

00:29:13.850 --> 00:29:14.650 align:middle line:90%
I was there.

00:29:14.650 --> 00:29:17.730 align:middle line:90%
That day, it was 105 degrees.

00:29:17.730 --> 00:29:20.630 align:middle line:84%
And the only other people
we had seen were family,

00:29:20.630 --> 00:29:23.690 align:middle line:84%
and we waited until they
were completely gone

00:29:23.690 --> 00:29:26.870 align:middle line:84%
because I don't like
anyone in the background

00:29:26.870 --> 00:29:28.320 align:middle line:90%
when I'm doing my stuff.

00:29:28.320 --> 00:29:31.760 align:middle line:84%
And so I was sure that
I was completely alone

00:29:31.760 --> 00:29:33.150 align:middle line:90%
there that day.

00:29:33.150 --> 00:29:35.330 align:middle line:84%
And we didn't hear
the crying until later

00:29:35.330 --> 00:29:37.820 align:middle line:84%
when we were reviewing
my little history tidbit.

00:29:37.820 --> 00:29:41.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There seems to be a
lot of pain at these sites.

00:29:41.670 --> 00:29:42.470 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:29:42.470 --> 00:29:44.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You feel that
when you're there?

00:29:44.000 --> 00:29:44.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I do.

00:29:44.750 --> 00:29:45.550 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:29:45.550 --> 00:29:49.220 align:middle line:84%
You feel-- you feel pain,
and you feel sadness,

00:29:49.220 --> 00:29:51.110 align:middle line:90%
and you feel fear.

00:29:51.110 --> 00:29:53.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're
scared too, then?

00:29:53.150 --> 00:29:55.640 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I'm not scared of
them, but I feel their fear.

00:29:55.640 --> 00:29:58.070 align:middle line:84%
Their fear of not
knowing what to expect

00:29:58.070 --> 00:30:01.140 align:middle line:84%
and not knowing that this
would be the end for them.

00:30:01.140 --> 00:30:04.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why are they
reaching out to you?

00:30:04.040 --> 00:30:05.540 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I've
spent a lot of time

00:30:05.540 --> 00:30:06.980 align:middle line:90%
trying to reach out to them.

00:30:06.980 --> 00:30:10.400 align:middle line:84%
And I try to be understanding
to them and their story.

00:30:10.400 --> 00:30:13.110 align:middle line:84%
And I tell them I want
their stories to be shared.

00:30:13.110 --> 00:30:15.680 align:middle line:84%
And I think they
know that I will

00:30:15.680 --> 00:30:18.560 align:middle line:84%
do my best to share the
tales of who they are

00:30:18.560 --> 00:30:22.290 align:middle line:84%
and what they meant and
what happened to them.

00:30:22.290 --> 00:30:25.040 align:middle line:84%
And so that way, their soul
might have a little peace.

00:30:25.040 --> 00:30:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You would think
after almost 200 years,

00:30:28.430 --> 00:30:30.860 align:middle line:84%
they had had enough of
this, but they don't.

00:30:30.860 --> 00:30:33.110 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Time doesn't
work that way, I don't think,

00:30:33.110 --> 00:30:33.910 align:middle line:90%
for them.

00:30:33.910 --> 00:30:37.280 align:middle line:84%
For them, it could have been
as soon as yesterday in the way

00:30:37.280 --> 00:30:38.270 align:middle line:90%
that time works.

00:30:38.270 --> 00:30:41.330 align:middle line:84%
And for us, it's
hundreds of years,

00:30:41.330 --> 00:30:43.330 align:middle line:90%
but they don't feel that.

00:30:43.330 --> 00:30:46.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: These spirits,
as they reach out to you--

00:30:46.070 --> 00:30:46.870 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:30:46.870 --> 00:30:49.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --do they talk
to you, or do they just

00:30:49.600 --> 00:30:52.580 align:middle line:84%
do it in song and
symbols and you know?

00:30:52.580 --> 00:30:53.380 align:middle line:90%
- It depends.

00:30:53.380 --> 00:30:55.750 align:middle line:84%
So you heard General
Mansfield spoke,

00:30:55.750 --> 00:30:58.570 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes when I'm
there, if I'm really focused,

00:30:58.570 --> 00:31:01.990 align:middle line:84%
I can almost hear the voices
of them or answering me.

00:31:01.990 --> 00:31:04.780 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of times,
it's them leading me

00:31:04.780 --> 00:31:09.130 align:middle line:84%
to information or something
of that nature that

00:31:09.130 --> 00:31:11.500 align:middle line:90%
allows me to find more.

00:31:11.500 --> 00:31:14.800 align:middle line:84%
But I try to record conversation
with them as much as I can.

00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do they visit
you at home, or always

00:31:16.930 --> 00:31:19.570 align:middle line:90%
on scenes and sites?

00:31:19.570 --> 00:31:21.670 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: You know,
I think they do.

00:31:21.670 --> 00:31:22.970 align:middle line:90%
I live in an old house.

00:31:22.970 --> 00:31:25.720 align:middle line:84%
And I decorate it with
pictures of all of the people

00:31:25.720 --> 00:31:26.800 align:middle line:90%
that I write about too.

00:31:26.800 --> 00:31:29.810 align:middle line:84%
So I probably honor
them in that way.

00:31:29.810 --> 00:31:33.100 align:middle line:84%
And we do have doors open
and shut and footsteps.

00:31:33.100 --> 00:31:34.810 align:middle line:90%
But I live in a very old home.

00:31:34.810 --> 00:31:36.640 align:middle line:84%
And my husband always
says to me, Courtney,

00:31:36.640 --> 00:31:37.890 align:middle line:90%
you're taking them home again.

00:31:37.890 --> 00:31:38.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, it's fine.

00:31:38.980 --> 00:31:40.928 align:middle line:84%
They're just passing
through saying hello.

00:31:40.928 --> 00:31:43.095 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, what does
hubby think about all this?

00:31:43.095 --> 00:31:44.270 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: [LAUGHS]
He's really good.

00:31:44.270 --> 00:31:46.460 align:middle line:84%
He's the man behind the
camera, God bless him.

00:31:46.460 --> 00:31:50.160 align:middle line:84%
So he's really good, and
he gets really excited.

00:31:50.160 --> 00:31:53.090 align:middle line:84%
He found that cry and
immediately called me

00:31:53.090 --> 00:31:54.890 align:middle line:84%
when he was reviewing
the footage.

00:31:54.890 --> 00:31:57.050 align:middle line:84%
He loves history,
and he and I both

00:31:57.050 --> 00:31:59.960 align:middle line:84%
had ancestors in all of
these wars and things

00:31:59.960 --> 00:32:01.080 align:middle line:90%
that I write about.

00:32:01.080 --> 00:32:03.980 align:middle line:84%
So we kind of like the idea
that we're touching base

00:32:03.980 --> 00:32:05.120 align:middle line:90%
with our own past.

00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:07.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you hear these
sounds, Courtney, when

00:32:07.190 --> 00:32:09.853 align:middle line:90%
you're there live in the field?

00:32:09.853 --> 00:32:11.270 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So the
drumming I did.

00:32:11.270 --> 00:32:12.020 align:middle line:90%
The drumming I did.

00:32:12.020 --> 00:32:13.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You hear it
in the background.

00:32:13.160 --> 00:32:14.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I heard
it in the background.

00:32:14.180 --> 00:32:15.890 align:middle line:84%
I've heard cannons
in the background,

00:32:15.890 --> 00:32:17.510 align:middle line:90%
gunfire in the background.

00:32:17.510 --> 00:32:19.700 align:middle line:84%
I've heard people talking
in the background.

00:32:19.700 --> 00:32:22.650 align:middle line:84%
The cry just took
me by surprise.

00:32:22.650 --> 00:32:24.320 align:middle line:90%
I didn't hear that that day.

00:32:24.320 --> 00:32:25.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you
ever hear shouts?

00:32:25.790 --> 00:32:26.690 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:32:26.690 --> 00:32:28.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Go get him,
things like that?

00:32:28.580 --> 00:32:30.997 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah, they would
often say that to each other.

00:32:30.997 --> 00:32:32.760 align:middle line:84%
Go get 'em boys and
things like that.

00:32:32.760 --> 00:32:34.010 align:middle line:90%
And you can hear those shouts.

00:32:34.010 --> 00:32:38.210 align:middle line:84%
You can hear what sounds like
a battle cry or a rebel yell.

00:32:38.210 --> 00:32:40.640 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, we'll hear a
lot of that sound coming

00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:43.670 align:middle line:84%
from the woods, which was
iconic for the Confederates.

00:32:43.670 --> 00:32:46.402 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are the
spirits expect from you?

00:32:46.402 --> 00:32:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I don't know that
they expect anything from me,

00:32:48.860 --> 00:32:52.040 align:middle line:84%
but I think they hope that
I will share their legacy.

00:32:52.040 --> 00:32:53.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're contacting
you for a reason.

00:32:53.930 --> 00:32:54.590 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I know.

00:32:54.590 --> 00:32:55.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There must
be something going on.

00:32:55.490 --> 00:32:58.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I don't want
to put anything on them.

00:32:58.080 --> 00:33:01.580 align:middle line:84%
I think that their hope is
that their legacy doesn't die

00:33:01.580 --> 00:33:02.990 align:middle line:90%
and that I can help them.

00:33:02.990 --> 00:33:04.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And have you?

00:33:04.490 --> 00:33:07.310 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I've been
writing many books.

00:33:07.310 --> 00:33:10.400 align:middle line:84%
So I've written two books
about the Civil War soldiers

00:33:10.400 --> 00:33:12.440 align:middle line:84%
and one about the
Revolutionary War.

00:33:12.440 --> 00:33:13.730 align:middle line:90%
And I'm still going.

00:33:13.730 --> 00:33:16.520 align:middle line:84%
And I'm still going there all
the time to talk about them

00:33:16.520 --> 00:33:19.290 align:middle line:84%
and make sure that people know
their stories and who they are.

00:33:19.290 --> 00:33:22.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What kind of people go
on these haunted history tours?

00:33:22.830 --> 00:33:24.980 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Oh, everybody.

00:33:24.980 --> 00:33:28.220 align:middle line:84%
I like to think that there's
something for everyone

00:33:28.220 --> 00:33:30.685 align:middle line:84%
on these tours and
in these books,

00:33:30.685 --> 00:33:32.810 align:middle line:84%
whether it's people who
are interested in their own

00:33:32.810 --> 00:33:34.925 align:middle line:84%
history, they're interested
in ghost stories,

00:33:34.925 --> 00:33:36.800 align:middle line:84%
they're interested in
understanding something

00:33:36.800 --> 00:33:38.030 align:middle line:90%
that happened to them.

00:33:38.030 --> 00:33:39.800 align:middle line:84%
But hopefully, it's
someone who wants

00:33:39.800 --> 00:33:43.250 align:middle line:84%
to know where we came from and
how it still resonates today.

00:33:43.250 --> 00:33:46.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you ever get reports
of lights in the area, UFO type

00:33:46.880 --> 00:33:48.150 align:middle line:90%
things or anything like that?

00:33:48.150 --> 00:33:48.950 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yes.

00:33:48.950 --> 00:33:49.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You do?

00:33:49.550 --> 00:33:50.120 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I do.

00:33:50.120 --> 00:33:50.920 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:33:50.920 --> 00:33:56.840 align:middle line:84%
So I will fully admit to you
I am very focused on my ghosts

00:33:56.840 --> 00:33:57.980 align:middle line:90%
from the past.

00:33:57.980 --> 00:34:00.800 align:middle line:84%
However, it seems
that a lot of times

00:34:00.800 --> 00:34:04.670 align:middle line:84%
where one paranormal thing
resides, other things

00:34:04.670 --> 00:34:06.980 align:middle line:90%
reside too.

00:34:06.980 --> 00:34:09.050 align:middle line:84%
During COVID, I
started researching

00:34:09.050 --> 00:34:14.150 align:middle line:84%
an area that had this infamous
axe murder by a madman.

00:34:14.150 --> 00:34:16.699 align:middle line:84%
And then I noticed
there were other legends

00:34:16.699 --> 00:34:22.260 align:middle line:84%
of Native American creatures,
of UFOs, things like that.

00:34:22.260 --> 00:34:23.460 align:middle line:90%
And that was intriguing.

00:34:23.460 --> 00:34:27.590 align:middle line:84%
And then it sort of came right
into my own backyard in Mystic.

00:34:27.590 --> 00:34:32.310 align:middle line:84%
I was training a tour guide,
and he was facing the audience.

00:34:32.310 --> 00:34:33.500 align:middle line:90%
And I was in the audience.

00:34:33.500 --> 00:34:35.520 align:middle line:84%
And above his head,
way up in the sky,

00:34:35.520 --> 00:34:38.120 align:middle line:90%
I saw these three red lights.

00:34:38.120 --> 00:34:40.310 align:middle line:90%
And they were enormous.

00:34:40.310 --> 00:34:42.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did he see
them too or just you?

00:34:42.360 --> 00:34:44.510 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I was the only one
facing it because they were all

00:34:44.510 --> 00:34:45.230 align:middle line:90%
looking at him.

00:34:45.230 --> 00:34:46.050 align:middle line:90%
And I looked up.

00:34:46.050 --> 00:34:47.925 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, he'd have
to look up and back.

00:34:47.925 --> 00:34:50.630 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: And I saw
them, and they went away.

00:34:50.630 --> 00:34:53.517 align:middle line:84%
And I whispered to my husband
because I had him over.

00:34:53.517 --> 00:34:54.350 align:middle line:90%
I said, did you see?

00:34:54.350 --> 00:34:56.142 align:middle line:84%
He said, no, I was
paying attention to him.

00:34:56.142 --> 00:34:59.900 align:middle line:84%
And I said, shoot, there
were these lights up there.

00:34:59.900 --> 00:35:03.680 align:middle line:84%
But I do enough ghosts, I
don't have room for UFOs too.

00:35:03.680 --> 00:35:05.520 align:middle line:84%
And he said, you
know, let's look up

00:35:05.520 --> 00:35:06.770 align:middle line:90%
and see if anyone else saw it.

00:35:06.770 --> 00:35:09.560 align:middle line:84%
And we saw that someone
else did reported it

00:35:09.560 --> 00:35:11.360 align:middle line:90%
online at the same time.

00:35:11.360 --> 00:35:13.200 align:middle line:90%
And I wasn't sure what it was.

00:35:13.200 --> 00:35:16.610 align:middle line:84%
And then a couple of weeks
later, one of my tour guides

00:35:16.610 --> 00:35:21.050 align:middle line:84%
got a photo taken on his
tour from a guest of what

00:35:21.050 --> 00:35:26.300 align:middle line:84%
appeared to be this UFO type
anomaly in the sky just sitting

00:35:26.300 --> 00:35:27.410 align:middle line:90%
over the Mystic River.

00:35:27.410 --> 00:35:29.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Clearly,
something was there.

00:35:29.060 --> 00:35:29.570 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Something was there.

00:35:29.570 --> 00:35:30.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Clearly.

00:35:30.170 --> 00:35:30.500 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:35:30.500 --> 00:35:31.542 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whatever it was.

00:35:31.542 --> 00:35:33.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Whatever
it was, yeah.

00:35:33.080 --> 00:35:36.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Who is, what
is your favorite ghost?

00:35:36.050 --> 00:35:40.240 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: My favorite
ghost, it's so hard to pick.

00:35:40.240 --> 00:35:43.662 align:middle line:84%
I love-- I love
them all so much.

00:35:43.662 --> 00:35:45.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You've become
friends with them.

00:35:45.370 --> 00:35:47.050 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I know,
and I feel bad if I,

00:35:47.050 --> 00:35:49.177 align:middle line:90%
like, favor any of them.

00:35:49.177 --> 00:35:51.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're listening
to you right now.

00:35:51.010 --> 00:35:51.580 align:middle line:90%
You know that.

00:35:51.580 --> 00:35:51.736 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I know.

00:35:51.736 --> 00:35:52.300 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:35:52.300 --> 00:35:54.540 align:middle line:84%
They're listening thinking,
who is she going to say?

00:35:54.540 --> 00:35:55.340 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is it me?

00:35:55.340 --> 00:35:56.140 align:middle line:90%
Is it me?

00:35:56.140 --> 00:35:59.260 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: [LAUGHS]
I have so many

00:35:59.260 --> 00:36:01.420 align:middle line:90%
for so many different reasons.

00:36:01.420 --> 00:36:03.760 align:middle line:84%
The Brooks brothers always
have a place in my heart

00:36:03.760 --> 00:36:05.440 align:middle line:90%
for leading me forward.

00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:07.100 align:middle line:84%
There were some
brothers from Georgia,

00:36:07.100 --> 00:36:08.770 align:middle line:84%
which is where my
dad was from, that

00:36:08.770 --> 00:36:11.950 align:middle line:84%
led me to write about
Georgia, the Jeffers brothers.

00:36:11.950 --> 00:36:13.580 align:middle line:84%
So those are some
of my favorites.

00:36:13.580 --> 00:36:15.460 align:middle line:84%
But I also have a
lot of encounters

00:36:15.460 --> 00:36:20.500 align:middle line:84%
with the spirits of
generals like Mansfield,

00:36:20.500 --> 00:36:24.970 align:middle line:84%
like Nathaniel Lyon, and on
the Confederate side, Stonewall

00:36:24.970 --> 00:36:27.580 align:middle line:84%
Jackson, Robert E. Lee,
a whole bunch of them.

00:36:27.580 --> 00:36:30.880 align:middle line:84%
I've just had
interesting encounters.

00:36:30.880 --> 00:36:33.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
recommend to people, Courtney,

00:36:33.190 --> 00:36:36.010 align:middle line:84%
who encounter a
ghost, they don't have

00:36:36.010 --> 00:36:38.630 align:middle line:90%
any experience handling ghosts.

00:36:38.630 --> 00:36:40.770 align:middle line:84%
They may not even
know what they are,

00:36:40.770 --> 00:36:42.628 align:middle line:84%
but what do you
recommend they do?

00:36:42.628 --> 00:36:44.045 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: If
they encounter one.

00:36:44.045 --> 00:36:45.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: If they encounter one.

00:36:45.680 --> 00:36:47.120 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I
recommend that they

00:36:47.120 --> 00:36:49.520 align:middle line:84%
treat them with
respect and kindness

00:36:49.520 --> 00:36:52.130 align:middle line:84%
and try not to
respond with fear.

00:36:52.130 --> 00:36:55.130 align:middle line:84%
When we respond with
fear, we get fear back

00:36:55.130 --> 00:36:57.110 align:middle line:90%
or the energy sort of becomes--

00:36:57.110 --> 00:36:58.610 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:36:58.610 --> 00:36:59.750 align:middle line:90%
Funky in a way.

00:36:59.750 --> 00:37:05.030 align:middle line:84%
If you respond just like they
would have responded to you

00:37:05.030 --> 00:37:06.973 align:middle line:90%
if they saw each other alive.

00:37:06.973 --> 00:37:08.390 align:middle line:84%
So I tell people,
you're not going

00:37:08.390 --> 00:37:10.010 align:middle line:84%
to walk into a
living person's house

00:37:10.010 --> 00:37:13.470 align:middle line:84%
and start acting weird around
them and demanding things.

00:37:13.470 --> 00:37:17.490 align:middle line:84%
So if you encounter a spirit,
ask them who they are,

00:37:17.490 --> 00:37:20.520 align:middle line:84%
what their name
is, what they need,

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:22.370 align:middle line:90%
and try to have a conversation.

00:37:22.370 --> 00:37:24.270 align:middle line:90%
And try to keep it peaceful.

00:37:24.270 --> 00:37:27.650 align:middle line:84%
And then let them know
that they can move along,

00:37:27.650 --> 00:37:30.030 align:middle line:84%
or they can stick around
if it's up to you.

00:37:30.030 --> 00:37:32.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you miss
work with the FBI?

00:37:32.070 --> 00:37:32.870 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: No.

00:37:32.870 --> 00:37:33.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Not at all.

00:37:33.770 --> 00:37:34.310 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Not at all.

00:37:34.310 --> 00:37:36.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Since you
replaced it with this.

00:37:36.140 --> 00:37:38.490 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Not at all.

00:37:38.490 --> 00:37:40.640 align:middle line:90%
I actually never looked back.

00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:43.520 align:middle line:84%
I think this is the path I
was always meant to be on.

00:37:43.520 --> 00:37:47.010 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just grateful at all the
experiences that led me here.

00:37:47.010 --> 00:37:48.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How do people find you?

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:52.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: So people can find
me through Seaside Shadows.

00:37:52.910 --> 00:37:57.500 align:middle line:84%
People can find me on my author
website courtneymcinvale.com.

00:37:57.500 --> 00:38:00.500 align:middle line:84%
And they can correspond
with me, check out my books,

00:38:00.500 --> 00:38:02.480 align:middle line:84%
and see what events
I have going on.

00:38:02.480 --> 00:38:04.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what's
next for you, Courtney?

00:38:04.520 --> 00:38:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: What's
next is I'm going

00:38:06.380 --> 00:38:09.860 align:middle line:84%
to keep cultivating events
where we can share haunted

00:38:09.860 --> 00:38:11.810 align:middle line:84%
stories with
people, but I'm also

00:38:11.810 --> 00:38:14.570 align:middle line:84%
going to keep writing those
books and sharing those stories

00:38:14.570 --> 00:38:20.750 align:middle line:84%
and ensuring that the heartbeats
of history are remembered.

00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:23.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I look at you,
and I see someone who

00:38:23.420 --> 00:38:25.200 align:middle line:90%
loves doing what you're doing.

00:38:25.200 --> 00:38:26.210 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I do.

00:38:26.210 --> 00:38:27.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's not
a game with you.

00:38:27.920 --> 00:38:28.880 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: No.

00:38:28.880 --> 00:38:31.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you take
it darn seriously.

00:38:31.050 --> 00:38:31.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I do.

00:38:31.850 --> 00:38:32.650 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:38:32.650 --> 00:38:35.453 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you ever
emotionally gotten upset--

00:38:35.453 --> 00:38:36.620 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Oh my gosh, yes.

00:38:36.620 --> 00:38:38.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --on a tour
or something like that?

00:38:38.510 --> 00:38:40.070 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE:
Generally, on a tour,

00:38:40.070 --> 00:38:41.970 align:middle line:90%
I can usually keep it together.

00:38:41.970 --> 00:38:45.800 align:middle line:84%
But when I'm writing stories
or I'm investigating on my own,

00:38:45.800 --> 00:38:47.730 align:middle line:90%
sometimes I've definitely cried.

00:38:47.730 --> 00:38:48.800 align:middle line:90%
I've felt sadness.

00:38:48.800 --> 00:38:52.700 align:middle line:84%
I read a story, I'll tell
you, and I wrote about it,

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:54.950 align:middle line:84%
about a dog that
followed these soldiers

00:38:54.950 --> 00:38:58.010 align:middle line:84%
around throughout the whole war
as this sort of spirit guide.

00:38:58.010 --> 00:38:59.720 align:middle line:84%
He appeared when
they needed him.

00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:03.560 align:middle line:84%
He stayed till the very end,
until shrapnel just hit him out

00:39:03.560 --> 00:39:04.550 align:middle line:90%
of nowhere.

00:39:04.550 --> 00:39:07.490 align:middle line:84%
And I cried reading that
whole story and the three page

00:39:07.490 --> 00:39:11.600 align:middle line:84%
obituary these soldiers wrote
about the soul of this dog.

00:39:11.600 --> 00:39:14.060 align:middle line:90%
Just they are people like us.

00:39:14.060 --> 00:39:15.620 align:middle line:90%
They have these stories like us.

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:22.190 align:middle line:84%
And it definitely makes me feel
for them and gets me emotional.

00:39:22.190 --> 00:39:26.680 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what would you
tell people who don't believe?

00:39:26.680 --> 00:39:27.940 align:middle line:90%
What do you say to them?

00:39:27.940 --> 00:39:31.900 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I say, that's fine,
just stay open and remember

00:39:31.900 --> 00:39:33.010 align:middle line:90%
that your ancestors--

00:39:33.010 --> 00:39:34.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And stay away.

00:39:34.090 --> 00:39:36.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: [LAUGHS]
Stay open and I

00:39:36.280 --> 00:39:39.190 align:middle line:84%
remind them your ancestors
believed in a soul that

00:39:39.190 --> 00:39:40.720 align:middle line:90%
lived separately from the body.

00:39:40.720 --> 00:39:43.300 align:middle line:84%
What you call it, what you
name it doesn't matter,

00:39:43.300 --> 00:39:45.730 align:middle line:84%
but there's an essence
and an energy to us,

00:39:45.730 --> 00:39:47.230 align:middle line:90%
and it never goes away.

00:39:47.230 --> 00:39:49.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you have
relatives at Gettysburg?

00:39:49.360 --> 00:39:50.960 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I did.

00:39:50.960 --> 00:39:51.760 align:middle line:90%
I did.

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:52.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what
happened to them?

00:39:52.700 --> 00:39:54.380 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Some of my
three-times great grandfathers

00:39:54.380 --> 00:39:55.520 align:middle line:90%
were there.

00:39:55.520 --> 00:39:57.982 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Did they pass--

00:39:57.982 --> 00:39:58.940 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: I did have.

00:39:58.940 --> 00:39:59.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --there.

00:39:59.740 --> 00:40:02.090 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: The ones that
fought at Gettysburg, actually

00:40:02.090 --> 00:40:03.890 align:middle line:84%
survived Gettysburg,
but I did have

00:40:03.890 --> 00:40:07.250 align:middle line:84%
a three-times great grandfather
who died in Manassas.

00:40:07.250 --> 00:40:10.030 align:middle line:90%
And he was only 21 years old.

00:40:10.030 --> 00:40:11.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So what
recommendation would

00:40:11.590 --> 00:40:15.400 align:middle line:84%
you give to people
who have children,

00:40:15.400 --> 00:40:21.040 align:middle line:84%
and they want them to learn
things about American history?

00:40:21.040 --> 00:40:22.630 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: I would
tell them, you

00:40:22.630 --> 00:40:24.700 align:middle line:84%
know what, bring
them right to it

00:40:24.700 --> 00:40:27.160 align:middle line:84%
because maybe they can
learn it from the source.

00:40:27.160 --> 00:40:31.330 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times, we can
utilize this fascination

00:40:31.330 --> 00:40:33.400 align:middle line:84%
with the supernatural
or the unknown

00:40:33.400 --> 00:40:36.790 align:middle line:84%
to help educate people
about what really happened

00:40:36.790 --> 00:40:39.700 align:middle line:84%
and to help history live
on in a way that's not just

00:40:39.700 --> 00:40:42.948 align:middle line:84%
numbers in a book but a
face and a name and a story.

00:40:42.948 --> 00:40:45.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You don't think you'd
scare the living daylights out

00:40:45.490 --> 00:40:46.630 align:middle line:90%
of the little ones?

00:40:46.630 --> 00:40:48.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: No, I think
tell them the story.

00:40:48.580 --> 00:40:51.550 align:middle line:84%
And then once they have a name
and they know that's a person,

00:40:51.550 --> 00:40:52.870 align:middle line:90%
they won't be too scared.

00:40:52.870 --> 00:40:55.540 align:middle line:84%
They'll be happy that someone
from the past was there.

00:40:55.540 --> 00:40:59.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The pain, though,
that must be at Gettysburg

00:40:59.410 --> 00:41:00.490 align:middle line:90%
is unbelievable.

00:41:00.490 --> 00:41:03.040 align:middle line:84%
Because I have heard
from other sources too--

00:41:03.040 --> 00:41:03.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Mm-hmm

00:41:03.850 --> 00:41:06.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --of people
who have witnessed

00:41:06.340 --> 00:41:08.420 align:middle line:90%
seeing the ghosts of soldiers.

00:41:08.420 --> 00:41:09.520 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:41:09.520 --> 00:41:11.125 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The
screams of soldiers.

00:41:11.125 --> 00:41:11.925 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:41:11.925 --> 00:41:13.340 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The pain, the agony.

00:41:13.340 --> 00:41:14.140 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: Yeah.

00:41:14.140 --> 00:41:15.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It was a horrible
time in this country.

00:41:15.960 --> 00:41:17.127 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: It was horrible.

00:41:17.127 --> 00:41:20.900 align:middle line:84%
It was the deadliest
battle of the Civil War.

00:41:20.900 --> 00:41:24.560 align:middle line:84%
The Civil War had 640,000
casualties in four years,

00:41:24.560 --> 00:41:28.340 align:middle line:84%
and Gettysburg had
near 50,000 casualties

00:41:28.340 --> 00:41:29.932 align:middle line:84%
over these three
days, casualties,

00:41:29.932 --> 00:41:31.640 align:middle line:84%
including wounded and
missing, of course.

00:41:31.640 --> 00:41:32.440 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure,

00:41:32.440 --> 00:41:36.320 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: But
to me, Gettysburg

00:41:36.320 --> 00:41:39.060 align:middle line:84%
is a perfect example
of a residual haunt.

00:41:39.060 --> 00:41:41.660 align:middle line:90%
So I tell people to take heart.

00:41:41.660 --> 00:41:44.720 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean that the
spirits are there in agony.

00:41:44.720 --> 00:41:49.040 align:middle line:84%
It means that what
happened to them is still

00:41:49.040 --> 00:41:53.780 align:middle line:84%
replaying in the earth
there where we are in a way.

00:41:53.780 --> 00:41:56.597 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean that they
are there actively in pain.

00:41:56.597 --> 00:41:58.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Courtney, if
you had an opportunity

00:41:58.430 --> 00:42:01.670 align:middle line:84%
to talk to one ghost
from Gettysburg,

00:42:01.670 --> 00:42:04.920 align:middle line:90%
what would you tell him?

00:42:04.920 --> 00:42:09.390 align:middle line:84%
>>MCINVALE: Huh, oh my
gosh, it would probably

00:42:09.390 --> 00:42:13.320 align:middle line:90%
be General Iverson from Georgia.

00:42:13.320 --> 00:42:16.500 align:middle line:84%
And I would say, don't you dare
send those boys into those pits

00:42:16.500 --> 00:42:18.150 align:middle line:84%
because all of them
are going to die.

00:42:18.150 --> 00:42:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And it will be the
deadliest charge,

00:42:19.680 --> 00:42:22.180 align:middle line:84%
and your life will
change forever.

00:42:22.180 --> 00:42:24.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And he may
say it's too late.

00:42:24.650 --> 00:42:25.450 align:middle line:90%
>>MCINVALE: He may.

00:42:25.450 --> 00:42:29.920 align:middle line:84%
I think I accidentally
encountered General Iverson.

00:42:29.920 --> 00:42:32.230 align:middle line:84%
I saw a fearful spirit
right where the charge was.

00:42:32.230 --> 00:42:34.990 align:middle line:84%
It was the oldest recorded
story at Gettysburg.

00:42:34.990 --> 00:42:37.900 align:middle line:84%
He was a little out
of sorts, not himself.

00:42:37.900 --> 00:42:40.600 align:middle line:84%
Some say he was drunk because
his wife had just died,

00:42:40.600 --> 00:42:43.720 align:middle line:84%
but he sent 900 men
in into a firing pit,

00:42:43.720 --> 00:42:44.950 align:middle line:90%
and they all died in minutes.

00:42:44.950 --> 00:42:47.380 align:middle line:84%
And they still rise
up out of those pits.

00:42:47.380 --> 00:42:50.860 align:middle line:84%
And when I was there, I saw the
face of a man in the darkness,

00:42:50.860 --> 00:42:54.568 align:middle line:84%
when my husband was away from
me, looking at me afraid that I

00:42:54.568 --> 00:42:56.860 align:middle line:84%
didn't realize till I was
looking at pictures of people

00:42:56.860 --> 00:42:58.310 align:middle line:90%
later, looked like him.

00:42:58.310 --> 00:43:01.240 align:middle line:84%
And when we got in the car
and we were driving away,

00:43:01.240 --> 00:43:03.400 align:middle line:84%
I could still see him
on the side of the car.

00:43:03.400 --> 00:43:05.440 align:middle line:84%
And the indicator
light was going off

